First Lady Melania Trump spoke at the Students against Destructive Decisions (SADD) National Conference, a 4-day training program for middle and high school students. She met with the SADD National Student Leadership Council, made blankets for a teen shelter, and listened to students share their stories. Mrs. Trump spoke on the importance of kindness, compassion, and positivity as part of her Be Best campaign. She emphasized the power of youth leadership and encouraged students to confront risks and pressures with confidence.